==Swedish==
===Verb===
'''focka''' ''-de , -t''
*[[Wiktionary:Swedish pronunciation|Pronunciation]]: {{IPAchar|/ˈfɔˌka/}}
#''(colloquial)'' To terminate someone's employment; to fire.
#:''Jag är rädd för att jag kommer bli '''fockad''' om jag kommer försent en gång till.''
#:"I'm afraid I'll get fired if I come to work late again."

====Etymology====
Since 1891. Student slang of disputed origin. Possibly related to dialectal Swedish ''fokka'' "fuck; thrust", related to [[fuck]].

